cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.DS 

This paper proposes a method for online adaptation of hyper-parameters in the CMA-ES algorithm, which is a widely used optimization algorithm in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of the CMA-ES algorithm in control systems (cs.SY) and optimization problems (cs.DS), which further supports these sub-categories as likely options.
